casebody.data:
JOHN V. STOCKTON v. ALFAR CREAMERY COMPANY, et al. 20 So. (2nd) 345

January Term, 1945

January 12, 1945 Division A Rehearing denied January 26, 1945 Carroll Dunscombe, for appellant. Paty & Warwick, for appellees. *411PER CURIAM:

The record and the arguments of counsel in this case have been considered. The questions are clear but they fail to convince us that the trial court committed error.

Affirmed.

CHAPMAN, C. J., TERRELL, BUFORD and ADAMS, JJ., concur.
